  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdminUpdate
    Only admins may update loans directly on the site, but this table keeps track of those updates and makes them reversible just in case.
    BannedUser
    An item in banned_users, these are users who have been banned by the loansbot from its respective subreddits.
    CreationInfo
    Describes by which process a loan was created.
    DelayedVettingRequest
    Describes a request to revisit vetting a user after a certain number of loans.
    FailedLoginAttempt
    Describes a saved login attempt
    Fullname
    Just a basic fullname that can be mapped to the database in order to prevent the bot from reusing the same one
    LendersCampContributor

    Recheck
    Describes a recheck
    RedFlag
    A red flag that is on a red flag report.
    RedFlagForSubreddit
    Describes a subreddit which when we see that a user has used we add a red flag.
    RedFlagQueueSpot
    Marks a spot in the queue for a username to have his history scanned and red flags reported.
    RedFlagReport
    This model serves as a centralized location to search for red flag reports
    RedFlagUserHistoryComment
    Describes a comment that a user made that was parsed during a red flag report.
    RedFlagUserHistoryLink
    Describes a link that was found while scanning a users history.
    RedFlagUserHistorySort
    We want to process the history for a user in a specific order, but we don't want to do an offset in our limit because we'll get to be verry slow if we pause many reports and resume near the end.
    Repayment
    Describes a repayment
    ResetPasswordRequest
    Describes a request to reset your password.
    Response
    Describes a response in the database
    ResponseHistory
    Responses are very flimsy; so we keep a good history on them.
    SavedQuery
    Contains the meta information about a saved query.
    SavedQueryParam
    Saved queries are actually broken up into several pieces, so having only one SavedQueryParam model isn't particularly useful.
    SavedQueryUser
    Many-to-Many relationship between saved queries and users
    ShareCode
    Describes a share code
    SiteSession
    This describes a session on the website.
    User
    Describes a user
    Username
    Since it is not uncommon for people to create multiple accounts, and this is not strictly against the rules (unless the other account has broken some rule), it is appropriate to have a way of sharing history between multiple users.
    Warning
    Describes a warning that was issued to a user
